# Top-level repo-tooling scripts (graphify-sync.sh, memory-stale-report.sh,
# promote-memory.sh) are invoked by systemd user units via their path inside
# the repo, not from $HOME. Keep stow from symlinking them into $HOME.
^/[^/]+\.sh$

# Stow's built-in ignore list is replaced once this file exists, so re-state
# the defaults we still want (README/LICENSE ignored at the package root, plus
# VCS and editor cruft).
\.git
\.gitignore
.+~
\#.*\#
^/README.*
^/LICENSE.*
^/COPYING
